var PI = 3.14;
PI = 42; // stop me from doing this!

/* Write an ES2015 Version */

const PI = 3.14

What is the difference between var and let?
Var allows you to redeclare the same variable, but let does not.

What is the difference between var and const?
Var allows you to redeclare and reassign the same variable, while const does not allow either.

What is the difference between let and const?
You can reassign values to a variable with let, but not with const. With let, you can declare a variable without assigning at the same time; with const, you have to assign when you declare a variable.

What is hoisting?
Hoisting occurs with var, and it means that javascript will access variables at the top of their scope, even before they are used in the code.